e to copy the SunOS NFS response to this case.<br />&gt; &gt; Its part of a more general lack of ability to pass errors back cleanly<br />&gt; &gt; issue. Its going to attack us for NFS write behind too<br />&gt; <br />&gt; I'm not sure what the "SunOS NFS response" is.  I'd be willing to copy<br />&gt; it if I did.  However, in my mind, the best solution would be to<br />&gt; change the VFS close() [oops -- release()] method to return an int<br />&gt; instead of returning void.  Then the filesystem would have a way to<br />&gt; return errors.<br /><br />This _will_ be done - I'm actually expecting patches for this from Olaf<br />Kirch some day soon for the NFS code (needed for write-behind). He's done<br />all this already I'm told.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
